featured_reviews.review_id: Jama Masjid is a very old mosque in the city. Its beautifully built and was the biggest mosque when it was built. The architecture  is marvellous but the masonary materials used are cheap. Rather than using tiles or marble they plastered the walls and painted it with different shades of paint and painted quranic ayats on the entrance. overall they tried to create the grandeur of mughal buildings on a very flimsy budget and failed miserably. Garib shaher ki masjid.

Allah ta'la is tarikhi masjid ki hifazat farmae

featured_reviews.review_id:
160 year old ahle hadees masjid in malerkotla, punjab...

[11:40 PM, 12/5/2017] +91 98555 64440: Jama Masjid Ahle Hadees, Malerkotla, Punjab ki 1857 mein buniyad rakhi gayi. Moulana Sanaullah Amritsari jinho ne Mirza ghulam Ahmed Qadaini ko shikast di thi, wo yaha ke imam rahe hai. Aurte 160 saal se yaha ba jamat namaz ada kar rahi hai. Ahle Hadees jamat Hindustan mein bane wali sab se pheli jamat hai.

Jama Masjid AhleHadees, Malerkotla, Punjab established in 1857. Moulana Sanaullah Amritsari who defeated Mirza Ghulam Ahmed Qadiani, used to be Imam here.
Women have been offering Salah for the past 160 years.
It's clear AhleHadees have existed in India much before Saudi was formed. It's not a new methodology or group.

featured_reviews.review_id: When that political entity was reorganised in 1956, the territories of the erstwhile state of Malerkotla became part of Punjab.[1] It is located on the Sangrur-Ludhiana State Highway (no. 11) and lies on the secondary Ludhiana-Delhi railway line. It is about 50 kilometres (31 mi) from Ludhiana and 35 kilometres (22 mi) from Sangrur in Sangrur district.
